# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# GSD V6 — Environment Variables Template
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Copy this file to `.env` (NOT committed) and fill in your values.
# GSD does not auto-load `.env`; set these in your shell profile or
# Windows user environment so they persist across terminals.
#
# Verify set correctly:
#   node -e "console.log(Object.entries({ANTHROPIC_API_KEY:!!process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY,GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN:!!process.env.GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN}))"

# ── LLM / CLI auth ──────────────────────────────────────────
# CLI OAuth is primary ($0 marginal); API keys are backup for rate-limit cooldowns.
# Required when GSD_LLM_MODE=sdk OR when Claude CLI hits its rate limit.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-REPLACE_ME

# Optional — only used when Gemini CLI is unavailable and GSD routes to the Google API.
GEMINI_API_KEY=REPLACE_ME
GOOGLE_API_KEY=REPLACE_ME

# Optional — only used when Codex CLI is unavailable.
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-REPLACE_ME

# Emergency API fallbacks (pay-per-token) — only fires when all subscription CLIs
# and primary API fallbacks are simultaneously on cooldown. Usually unused.
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=REPLACE_ME
MINIMAX_API_KEY=REPLACE_ME

# NVIDIA Build (NIM) — free-tier inference for the V7.0 4th-family lane
# (qwen3-coder-480b, devstral-2-123b, llama-3.3-nemotron-super-49b, deepseek-v4
# via NIM, llama-4-maverick 1M context). Provision at https://build.nvidia.com
# Free tier ~1000 req/day. Pipeline gracefully falls back if unset.
NVIDIA_API_KEY=nvapi-REPLACE_ME

# ── GitHub MCP ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Fine-grained token with: repo (read/write), pull_requests, issues.
# Used by the GitHub MCP server declared in .claude/settings.json.
GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN=ghp_REPLACE_ME

# ── GSD runtime mode ────────────────────────────────────────
# GSD_LLM_MODE: "cli" (default) uses Claude Code OAuth; "sdk" forces ANTHROPIC_API_KEY.
# Leave unset for normal operation.
# GSD_LLM_MODE=cli

# ── Claude memory vault (v6.0.0+) ───────────────────────────
# Optional — overrides the default path if your OneDrive org name differs.
# Default: /c/Users/rjain/OneDrive - Technijian, Inc/Documents/obsidian/gsd-autonomous-dev/gsd-autonomous-dev/claude-memory
# GSD_VAULT_MEMORY=C:\Users\YOUR_USER\OneDrive - YOUR_ORG\Documents\obsidian\gsd-autonomous-dev\gsd-autonomous-dev\claude-memory

# ── Notes ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Do NOT commit `.env` — it is gitignored by convention (.env, .env.local).
# 2. On Windows, set these as USER env vars:
#      [System.Environment]::SetEnvironmentVariable('ANTHROPIC_API_KEY', 'sk-ant-...', 'User')
# 3. Target-project stack overrides live in `<target-project>/docs/gsd/stack-overrides.md`,
#    not in env vars. See `docs/stack-overrides-template.md`.
